MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/client/src/shells/pulse/components/input/PulseInput\.tsx
MATCH_CONTENT: AnimatePresence
ADVISORY: |
  PulseInput's command branches (command-picker / player-picker / amount-picker /
  preview / whisper / reply / idle) render as sibling conditionals inside the
  same flow container. Wrapping JUST ONE branch in AnimatePresence for an exit
  animation creates a layout race — the exiting branch stays mounted while the
  next branch (usually idle UI) renders beside it, producing double-height then
  snap-collapse when the exit completes.

  Session cost: three iterations on PlayerPicker dismiss — plain AnimatePresence
  had the stacking pop; mode="popLayout" instead made the parent snap to idle
  height while the picker was still fading (worse). The clean fix was dropping
  the exit animation entirely.

  Two safe patterns:
    1. Wrap ALL branches in a single AnimatePresence with keys on each
       (optionally mode="wait"), so sibling transitions coordinate.
    2. Skip exit animation entirely — instant unmount is clean against a
       conditional-render parent.

  Do NOT wrap just one branch while leaving the others bare.

  ADR-141 already governs view-transition composition with AnimatePresence
  for these panels (rules 4 + 5). Any new exit animation here must respect
  the `vtActive` gate from that ADR AND follow one of the two patterns above.
